    <description>Serial ports or emulated serial ports (typically, connected via USB) are used to communicate with many different types of devices. Examples include laboratory test equipment, machine tools, Arduino boards, external displays, etc.

To use a serial port, you must specify the port, baud rate, parity, number of data bits and number of stop bits. While the port and baud rate will vary, most devices use no parity, 8 data bits and 1 stop bit.

Event

Serial Listen

Triggers when the specified sequence of characters is received.



Reaction

Serial Write

Sends the specified sequence of characters.
</description>
<summary>These modules interact with devices using serial communication.</summary>
